 CellLabel->
  "In[122]:=",ExpressionUUID->"64711cfb-3806-488c-bd0d-2403e967b83a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "I now needed establish a formula for getting the coordinates of the next \
point in the tail using ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "adj"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "029f7d5c-6b5e-4ad2-81ce-1e8728271f0f"],
 ". To do this for the single jointed tail prior, I used trigonometry and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a2ee9de9-2537-434a-b5a8-6909f53909ac"],
 ". This works for ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "adj1"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "0b4067dd-4972-4bde-9a2e-1af725159f04"],
 " but no other subsequent angles. Thus, due to this discrepancy, I \
established a new variable type, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "n"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "b7aeda22-5d21-47cb-9e85-63762d939db1"],
 ". ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "n"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "de0fc00a-e122-4161-8587-0415e30c7e0e"],
 " is the angle of the triangle used to compute the next point of the line. \
In the model V2, what is now called ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "1"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "fdb7f64d-7770-4575-abe8-7e0f82c3fdff"],
 " had previously been computed as the following:"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9924182846744537`*^9, 3.992418319051136*^9}, {
   3.992418350578918*^9, 3.992418412636354*^9}, {3.992418475915766*^9, 
